## 3. TYPOGRAPHY — USE AppTypography EXCLUSIVELY

Import path: `lib/utils/app_typography.dart`
Font family: Inter (via google_fonts). Never set fontFamily manually.

| Style                     | Method                           | Size | Weight |
|---------------------------|----------------------------------|------|--------|
| Screen / page title       | AppTypography.heading1(context)  | 24sp | 700    |
| Section title             | AppTypography.heading2(context)  | 20sp | 600    |
| Card title / subsection   | AppTypography.heading3(context)  | 18sp | 600    |
| Primary body copy         | AppTypography.body(context)      | 16sp | 400    |
| Secondary body / list     | AppTypography.bodySmall(context) | 14sp | 400    |
| Metadata / hint / time    | AppTypography.caption(context)   | 12sp | 400    |
| Button labels             | AppTypography.button(context)    | 16sp | 500    |
| De-emphasized secondary   | AppTypography.secondary(context) | 14sp | 400    |
| Inline error messages     | AppTypography.error(context)     | 14sp | 400    |

### Typography Rules

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
Text('My Board', style: AppTypography.heading1(context))
Text('Last updated 2h ago', style: AppTypography.caption(context))

// ❌ WRONG — hardcoded size
Text('My Board', style: const TextStyle(fontSize: 24, fontWeight: FontWeight.bold))

// ❌ WRONG — hardcoded font family
Text('x', style: TextStyle(fontFamily: 'Inter', fontSize: 14))

// ❌ WRONG — fontSize below 12sp anywhere visible to users
Text('label', style: TextStyle(fontSize: 11))  // use caption() which is 12sp
```

Minimum text size: **12sp** (AppTypography.caption). Never go below this for
any user-visible label, badge count, or nav label.

Line height defaults are baked into AppTypography. Do not override `height`
unless you have a documented reason.

---

## 4. SPACING & LAYOUT

Use a consistent 4pt grid. All padding, margin, gap, and size values must be
multiples of 4.

### Standard Spacing Constants

```dart
// Preferred: define locally if not yet extracted to a constants file
static const double spaceXS = 4.0;
static const double spaceSM = 8.0;
static const double spaceMD = 16.0;
static const double spaceLG = 24.0;
static const double spaceXL = 32.0;
static const double space2XL = 48.0;
```

### Layout Rules

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT — 4pt grid
Padding(padding: const EdgeInsets.all(16))          // spaceMD
Padding(padding: const EdgeInsets.all(24))          // spaceLG
SizedBox(height: 8)                                 // spaceSM
SizedBox(height: 12)                                // acceptable (3×4)

// ❌ WRONG — off-grid values
Padding(padding: const EdgeInsets.all(15))
Padding(padding: const EdgeInsets.all(22))
SizedBox(height: 7)
```

### Border Radius

| Surface               | Radius |
|-----------------------|--------|
| Cards (cloudDecoration) | 24dp |
| Buttons               | 12dp   |
| Chips / tags          | 8dp    |
| Bottom sheets         | 24dp top corners |
| Dialogs               | 20dp   |
| Input fields          | 12dp   |
| Small badges          | 6dp    |

```dart
// ✅ For standard cards — always use cloudDecoration or GlassCard
Container(decoration: AppColors.cloudDecoration(isDark: isDark))

// ✅ For buttons
borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(12)

// ❌ Don't invent new radii
borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(10)  // use 12
borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(16)  // use 12 (btn) or 24 (card)
```

### Touch Targets

All interactive elements must be at least **48×48dp**. Wrap small icons with
`GestureDetector` or `InkWell` that has sufficient padding to meet this minimum.

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
SizedBox(
  width: 48,
  height: 48,
  child: IconButton(icon: Icon(Icons.close), onPressed: onClose),
)

// ❌ WRONG — bare Icon with tap handler, no size guarantee
GestureDetector(
  onTap: onClose,
  child: Icon(Icons.close, size: 18),
)
```

---

## 5. BACKGROUNDS & SURFACES — THE TWO-SURFACE RULE

Every screen in this app uses exactly ONE of two backgrounds:

### 5a. Full-Screen Scaffold

Always apply `AppColors.skyDecoration` to the Scaffold body:

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT pattern for every new screen
@override
Widget build(BuildContext context) {
  final isDark = Theme.of(context).brightness == Brightness.dark;
  return Scaffold(
    extendBodyBehindAppBar: true,
    body: Container(
      decoration: AppColors.skyDecoration(isDark: isDark),
      child: SafeArea(child: _buildContent(context)),
    ),
  );
}

// ❌ WRONG — bare white Scaffold (causes the "lavender ghost" issue)
return Scaffold(
  body: SafeArea(child: _buildContent(context)),
);

// ❌ WRONG — manual gradient (fragile, doesn't adapt to theme)
return Scaffold(
  backgroundColor: const Color(0xFFEEF7EE),
  ...
);
```

### 5b. Content Cards

Use one of the two card primitives. Do NOT mix them arbitrarily:

| Primitive          | When to use                                                    |
|--------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|
| `cloudDecoration`  | Cards on a solid/mist background (dashboard cards, list tiles, settings rows) |
| `GlassCard`        | Cards placed over a photographic or gradient/image background (vision board header, banner overlays) |

```dart
// ✅ Standard content card
Container(
  decoration: AppColors.cloudDecoration(isDark: isDark),
  padding: const EdgeInsets.all(16),
  child: content,
)

// ✅ Glass card over image background
GlassCard(child: content)

// ❌ WRONG — mixing card styles randomly
Container(
  decoration: BoxDecoration(
    color: Colors.white,
    borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(16),
    boxShadow: [...],  // re-inventing cloudDecoration
  ),
)
```

---

## 6. NAVIGATION

### Bottom Navigation

- Background: always `AppColors.forestDeep`
- Active icon + label: `AppColors.sproutGreen`
- Inactive icon + label: `AppColors.sproutGreen.withValues(alpha: 0.5)` (do NOT
  use grey or system defaults)
- Nav labels: `AppTypography.caption(context)` — minimum 12sp, NEVER 11sp

```dart
// ✅ Nav label — correct
Text(label, style: AppTypography.caption(context))

// ❌ WRONG — hardcoded below minimum
Text(label, style: const TextStyle(fontSize: 11, color: Colors.grey))
```

### AppBar

- Use `AppBar` with `backgroundColor: Colors.transparent` and
  `elevation: 0` for screens that use `skyDecoration` behind them.
- Title: `AppTypography.heading2(context)` or `heading3(context)`
- Leading action (close/back): always `Icons.close` or `Icons.arrow_back_ios_new`
  at 48dp touch target
- Trailing actions: icon buttons at 48dp; text actions use
  `AppTypography.button(context)` colored with `colorScheme.primary`

```dart
// ✅ Transparent app bar (most screens)
AppBar(
  backgroundColor: Colors.transparent,
  elevation: 0,
  title: Text('Write', style: AppTypography.heading2(context)),
  leading: IconButton(
    icon: const Icon(Icons.close),
    onPressed: Navigator.of(context).pop,
  ),
  actions: [
    TextButton(
      onPressed: _save,
      child: Text('Save', style: AppTypography.button(context)
          .copyWith(color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary)),
    ),
  ],
)
```

---

## 7. ACCESSIBILITY REQUIREMENTS

Every widget you write must satisfy these checks before it is considered done:

### 7a. Contrast Ratios

| Foreground on background combination          | Min ratio | Check        |
|-----------------------------------------------|-----------|--------------|
| Any body/heading text on mistBackground       | 4.5:1     | ✅ forestDeep on mist ≈ 12.5:1 — use it |
| Placeholder / hint text on mistBackground     | 3:1       | Use colorScheme.onSurfaceVariant |
| sproutGreen (#4CAF50) as TEXT on white        | —         | ❌ NEVER — use onPrimaryContainer instead |
| seedGold (#D4AF37) as TEXT on white           | —         | ❌ NEVER — use onTertiaryContainer instead |
| White text on sproutGreen button              | 4.5:1     | ✅ ~4.6:1 — acceptable for button labels |

### 7b. Semantics

Add `Semantics` labels to every custom interactive widget. The animated bottom
nav, custom toggle buttons, and drag handles are the most common offenders.

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
Semantics(
  label: 'Dashboard',
  button: true,
  selected: isActive,
  child: GestureDetector(onTap: onTap, child: navTabContent),
)

// Also use Tooltip on icon-only buttons
Tooltip(
  message: 'Flag entry',
  child: IconButton(icon: const Icon(Icons.flag_outlined), onPressed: onFlag),
)
```

### 7c. Text Scaling

Do NOT hard-cap text sizes with `maxLines: 1` without also providing a
`TextOverflow.ellipsis` and testing at 200% font scale. Never use
`MediaQuery.of(context).textScaleFactor` to manually shrink text.

---

## 8. COMPONENT PATTERNS

### 8a. Buttons

```dart
// Primary CTA — filled, forestDeep/sproutGreen theme
ElevatedButton(
  style: ElevatedButton.styleFrom(
    backgroundColor: colorScheme.primary,           // sproutGreen
    foregroundColor: colorScheme.onPrimary,          // white
    shape: RoundedRectangleBorder(
      borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(12),
    ),
    minimumSize: const Size.fromHeight(52),
    textStyle: AppTypography.button(context),
  ),
  onPressed: onPressed,
  child: Text(label),
)

// Secondary / outlined
OutlinedButton(
  style: OutlinedButton.styleFrom(
    foregroundColor: colorScheme.secondary,
    side: BorderSide(color: colorScheme.outline),
    shape: RoundedRectangleBorder(
      borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(12),
    ),
    minimumSize: const Size.fromHeight(52),
  ),
  onPressed: onPressed,
  child: Text(label),
)

// Destructive
ElevatedButton(
  style: ElevatedButton.styleFrom(
    backgroundColor: colorScheme.error,
    foregroundColor: colorScheme.onError,
    ...
  ),
  ...
)
```

### 8b. Input Fields

```dart
TextField(
  style: AppTypography.body(context),
  decoration: InputDecoration(
    hintText: 'Write your entry...',
    hintStyle: AppTypography.secondary(context),
    filled: true,
    fillColor: colorScheme.surfaceContainerLowest,
    border: OutlineInputBorder(
      borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(12),
      borderSide: BorderSide(color: colorScheme.outline),
    ),
    focusedBorder: OutlineInputBorder(
      borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(12),
      borderSide: BorderSide(color: colorScheme.primary, width: 2),
    ),
    contentPadding: const EdgeInsets.symmetric(horizontal: 16, vertical: 14),
  ),
)
```

### 8c. Chips & Tags

```dart
Chip(
  label: Text(label, style: AppTypography.caption(context)),
  backgroundColor: colorScheme.secondaryContainer,
  labelStyle: TextStyle(color: colorScheme.onSecondaryContainer),
  shape: RoundedRectangleBorder(
    borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(8),
  ),
  padding: const EdgeInsets.symmetric(horizontal: 8, vertical: 4),
)
```

### 8d. Empty States

Every list or content area that can be empty MUST have a designed empty state.
Pattern: large icon (64dp, colorScheme.outlineVariant) + heading2 + secondary
text + optional CTA button.

```dart
// Empty state template
Column(
  mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
  children: [
    Icon(icon, size: 64, color: colorScheme.outlineVariant),
    const SizedBox(height: 16),
    Text(title, style: AppTypography.heading2(context), textAlign: TextAlign.center),
    const SizedBox(height: 8),
    Text(subtitle, style: AppTypography.secondary(context), textAlign: TextAlign.center),
    if (onAction != null) ...[
      const SizedBox(height: 24),
      ElevatedButton(onPressed: onAction, child: Text(actionLabel)),
    ],
  ],
)
```

### 8e. Section Headers on Dashboard / Lists

```dart
Padding(
  padding: const EdgeInsets.fromLTRB(16, 24, 16, 8),
  child: Text(sectionTitle, style: AppTypography.heading3(context)),
)
```

