## 9. JOURNAL EDITOR — SPECIFIC RULES

The journal editor (`journal_editor_screen.dart`) has specific patterns:

- Background: `AppColors.skyDecoration(isDark: isDark)` applied to Scaffold body
- Toolbar: all formatting icons in a single `Row` with `Wrap` fallback; spacing
  between icons: 4dp (`spaceXS`); icon touch target: 40×40dp minimum
- Quote/blockquote button: place IN the toolbar row, not in a separate orphaned
  row. Add `Tooltip(message: 'Blockquote')`
- AppBar trailing: use an `IconButton` for flag/bookmark, and a separate
  `TextButton` for Save — do not combine them visually
- Writing area: `Colors.transparent` background, cursor color:
  `colorScheme.primary`, selectionHandleColor: `colorScheme.primary`

---

## 10. DASHBOARD — CARD DENSITY RULES

The dashboard must NOT render more than **5 visible cards** above the fold on a
standard 390pt-wide device. Rules:

1. Lead with the active vision board preview card (always first, full-width)
2. Follow with the user's most-active habit streak card
3. Third slot: daily affirmation or daily challenge (whichever is active)
4. Below-fold cards: water, calories, mood, journal, todos, etc.
5. Use a "Show more" / expansion pattern for secondary tracking cards — do not
   auto-render all 15 card types unless the user has explicitly pinned them

For every new dashboard card widget:
- Use `cloudDecoration`
- Internal padding: 16dp all sides
- Card title: `AppTypography.heading3(context)`
- Value / metric: `AppTypography.heading1(context)` or `heading2`
- Supporting label: `AppTypography.caption(context)`
- Min height: 80dp; max height before needing a "See more" link: 200dp

---

## 11. ANIMATIONS & MICRO-INTERACTIONS

- Duration: use one of 100ms / 200ms / 300ms / 500ms. Nothing else.
- Easing: `Curves.easeInOut` (default), `Curves.easeOut` (exit),
  `Curves.easeIn` (enter), `Curves.elasticOut` (delight/spring)
- Do NOT use `AnimationController` for things that can be done with
  `AnimatedContainer`, `AnimatedOpacity`, or `AnimatedSwitcher`
- The center + button pulse uses 1.0s with `Curves.easeInOut` — match this
  rhythm for any other pulsing/breathing animations

---

## 12. THEMING — NEVER BYPASS COLORSCHEME FOR CORE UI

The app supports light and dark themes. Every core UI widget MUST respond to
theme changes without requiring a rebuild-from-scratch.

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT — theme-aware
final colorScheme = Theme.of(context).colorScheme;
final isDark = colorScheme.brightness == Brightness.dark;

// ❌ WRONG — bypasses theme, breaks dark mode
final isDark = false;
final bg = Colors.white;
```

The ONLY places where `AppColors.*` constants (not colorScheme) are acceptable:
- `AppColors.forestDeep` for bottom nav background (intentionally fixed)
- `AppColors.skyDecoration()` and `AppColors.cloudDecoration()` which are
  already theme-aware internally
- `AppColors.categoryBgColor()` and `AppColors.categoryIconColor()` accessors
  (they accept `isDark` and handle both themes)

---

## 13. WHAT NOT TO BUILD

These patterns are explicitly prohibited — they have been identified as sources
of bugs, inconsistency, or failed accessibility checks:

| Pattern                                              | Why                                          |
|------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| `Text(x, style: TextStyle(fontSize: N))`            | Use AppTypography methods                    |
| `Container(color: Color(0xFFXXXXXX))`               | Use AppColors or colorScheme                 |
| `BoxDecoration(borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(N))` where N ∉ {6,8,12,20,24} | Off-system radius |
| `Scaffold(backgroundColor: anyColor)` without skyDecoration | Breaks background consistency          |
| `GestureDetector` on targets < 48×48dp              | Fails touch target minimums                  |
| `Text` with `color: AppColors.sproutGreen` or `seedGold` | Fails contrast on light backgrounds    |
| Legacy AppColors entries (soil, water, seed variants) | Use core palette only                      |
| `textScaleFactor` manipulation                       | Breaks accessibility scaling                 |
| Inline `BoxShadow` definitions outside of `cloudDecoration` | Breaks shadow consistency               |

---

## 14. FILE & WIDGET NAMING

- Screens: `*_screen.dart` — one `StatefulWidget` or `StatelessWidget` per file
- Reusable widgets: `*_card.dart`, `*_tile.dart`, `*_sheet.dart`, `*_dialog.dart`
- Place screen-specific helper widgets in `screens/<domain>/widgets/`
- Place shared widgets in `lib/widgets/<domain>/`
- `utils/` is for static helpers and constants only — no widgets

---

## 15. QUICK REFERENCE CHEATSHEET

```dart
// === Imports every new screen needs ===
import '../utils/app_colors.dart';
import '../utils/app_typography.dart';

// === Scaffold shell ===
final isDark = Theme.of(context).brightness == Brightness.dark;
final cs = Theme.of(context).colorScheme;

Scaffold(
  extendBodyBehindAppBar: true,
  body: Container(
    decoration: AppColors.skyDecoration(isDark: isDark),
    child: SafeArea(child: content),
  ),
)

// === Standard card ===
Container(
  decoration: AppColors.cloudDecoration(isDark: isDark),
  padding: const EdgeInsets.all(16),
  child: Column(
    crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.start,
    children: [
      Text(title, style: AppTypography.heading3(context)),
      const SizedBox(height: 8),
      Text(body, style: AppTypography.body(context)),
    ],
  ),
)

// === Primary button ===
ElevatedButton(
  style: ElevatedButton.styleFrom(
    backgroundColor: cs.primary,
    foregroundColor: cs.onPrimary,
    shape: RoundedRectangleBorder(borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(12)),
    minimumSize: const Size.fromHeight(52),
  ),
  onPressed: onPressed,
  child: Text(label, style: AppTypography.button(context)),
)
```
